description: Unlabeled (i.e. equivalent to their 1-0 complement) binary necklaces sorted in ascending lexicographic order and read as binary numbers.
links: F. Ruskey, Necklaces, Lyndon words, De Bruijn sequences, etc.
Index entries for sequences related to necklaces
example: a(5)=1 because it corresponds to the necklace 01; a(13)=5 because it corresponds to the necklace 0101.
author: Felix Goldberg (felixg(AT)tx.technion.ac.il), Jan 03 2001
